In the last step, the level of confidence is assessed depending on the number of evidence extracted (i.e., articles) and literature agreement (see the ‘evidence’, ‘agreement’ and ‘confidence’ cells in SM4 and Table 2
                        ). Very high confidence (5-stars) implies robust evidence and high agreement. Similarly, very low confidence (1-star) depicts both low literature agreement and evidence (Mastrandrea et al., 2010). Based on the scores and the level of confidence we create the SDG chart (see Fig. 2
                         in subsection 3.2) to visually represent the synergies and trade-offs for the two demand-side mitigation options with the SDGs.
